# .cursorignore
# BLUEPRINT: Composer 2 implements from this structure
# PURPOSE: Cursor IDE indexing exclusions for agent context. Excludes directories that add
#          noise without value to the agent's context window: caches, virtual environments,
#          build outputs, large binary files, and generated files.
#          Per spec §26.12 item 373.
# SECTIONS:
#   - Python caches and build artifacts
#   - Virtual environments
#   - IDE-specific directories
#   - Node modules (for optional web/mobile)
#   - Large generated files that are regenerated on demand
# DESIGN DECISIONS:
#   - .venv is excluded: agents should read pyproject.toml for deps, not scan installed packages
#   - __pycache__ excluded: not useful for understanding intent
#   - node_modules excluded: vast and not relevant to Python-first work
#   - htmlcov excluded: coverage HTML output is large and redundant with coverage.xml
#   - monitoring/grafana/dashboards/*.json excluded: large JSON blobs with no agent utility

# Python caches
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
.mypy_cache/
.pyright/
.pytest_cache/

# Virtual environments
.venv/
venv/
env/

# Build outputs
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/

# Coverage reports
htmlcov/
.coverage
coverage.xml

# Node
node_modules/
.npm/

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/

# OS
.DS_Store

# Large generated files (regenerated by make docs:generate or similar)
docs/api/openapi-baseline.json
monitoring/grafana/dashboards/api-overview.json

# Git internals
.git/
